      "url": "https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/40752867/",
      "content": "[Source: PubMed] Disease: Intellectual developmental disorder with dysmorphic facies and ptosis (IDDDFP)\n\nGenetics: BRPF1; inheritance pattern not specified\n\nKey Phenotypes:\n- Intellectual developmental disorder\n- Dysmorphic facial features\n- Ptosis (often congenital; can be unilateral or bilateral)\n\nDifferentiating Features:\n\nHallmark(s): \n- Combination of intellectual developmental disorder with characteristic dysmorphic facies and ptosis in the setting of a pathogenic BRPF1 variant\n\nKey Negative Finding(s): \n- Not specified\n\nUnique Constellation:\n- Intellectual developmental disorder + dysmorphic facies + congenital ptosis with a BRPF1 pathogenic variant strongly supports IDDDFP over other causes of congenital ptosis or nonspecific intellectual disability syndromes.",
      "disease_name": "INTELLECTUAL DEVELOPMENTAL DISORDER WITH DYSMORPHIC FACIES AND PTOSIS; IDDDFP"
