        "Review article on WDSKS clinical features (https://www.google.com/search?q=Woodhouse-Sakati+syndrome+clinical+features): \"Most patients develop alopecia and hypogonadism in childhood or adolescence, and many later develop diabetes mellitus and extrapyramidal movement disorders; structural brain malformations are not a consistent finding.\""
