        "Wikipedia (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chopra-Amiel-Gordon_Syndrome): \"Affected individuals typically have a distinctive craniofacial appearance with a triangular or elongated face, high anterior hairline, almond-shaped or deep-set eyes, full cheeks, thick nasal alae with flared nostrils, a thin upper vermilion, and low-set ears.\"",
        "Wikipedia (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chopra-Amiel-Gordon_Syndrome): \"Additional features may include cleft palate, Pierre Robin sequence, scoliosis, ophthalmologic abnormalities such as strabismus, refractive errors, or microphthalmia, growth impairment, feeding difficulties, recurrent bacterial or viral infections, joint hypermobility, and kidney anomalies.\"",
        "Wikipedia (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chopra-Amiel-Gordon_Syndrome): \"The combination of global developmental delay/intellectual disability with markedly severe speech delay and absence seizures, together with the characteristic facial gestalt and association with joint hypermobility, recurrent infections, and structural kidney anomalies, is considered a hallmark of ANKRD17 loss-of-function.\""
