        "Wikipedia – Schaaf–Yang syndrome (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Schaaf%E2%80%93Yang_syndrome): “Schaaf–Yang syndrome … is caused by mutations in the MAGEL2 gene… People with this condition have delayed development; intellectual disability; hypotonia; feeding problems… and joint contractures… Other features may include autism spectrum disorder; hypogonadism… truncal obesity and type 2 diabetes; scoliosis or kyphosis; sleep apnea; chronic constipation; and seizures.”",
