DiagnosisAnalysis: Evidence FOR NDH:
- There is no curated phenotypic description provided in the prompt, but by definition NDH involves an early-onset neurodevelopmental/endocrine disorder, so a few high-level, non-specific overlaps exist: global developmental delay, hypotonia, seizures, and failure to thrive are compatible with a broad range of congenital or neonatal-onset disorders, including some monogenic forms of diabetes or thyroid dysfunction.
